questions.scenario:
You are reviewing a 'Bug Hunter' scenario in a Spring Boot application. A developer implemented a custom `TransactionalList` that tracks changes for an audit log. However, the audit records are never saved to the database when `processBatch` is called. 

java
@Service
public class AuditService {
    @Transactional
    public void processBatch(List<String> data) {
        for (String item : data) {
            saveAudit(item);
        }
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void saveAudit(String log) {
        // Repository call to save audit record
        auditRepo.save(new AuditEntry(log));
    }
}
